WEBVTT

1
00:01:10.612 --> 00:01:12.530
Hey. I need my cast off.

2
00:01:12.614 --> 00:01:13.823
As soon as you
park that outside.

3
00:01:13.907 --> 00:01:15.533
- Morning. Doc.
- Olsen.

4
00:01:15.617 --> 00:01:16.951
Happy Fourth.

5
00:01:17.035 --> 00:01:18.620
Excuse me. guys.

6
00:01:18.703 --> 00:01:21.623
Sorry.

7
00:01:46.272 --> 00:01:47.982
Hey. how's it going. Dad?

8
00:01:48.066 --> 00:01:49.442
I'm so sleep-deprived.

9
00:01:49.526 --> 00:01:51.486
My house is starting to feel
like a CIA black site.

10
00:01:51.569 --> 00:01:53.446
Have you considered hiring
a night nurse?

11
00:01:53.530 --> 00:01:55.198
- You're looking at him.
- You got a ripe one coming in

12
00:01:55.281 --> 00:01:56.866
you're gonna have to deal with
before everybody out there

13
00:01:56.950 --> 00:01:58.284
- starts puking.
- Lovely.

14
00:01:58.368 --> 00:01:59.869
Your replacement came in early.

15
00:01:59.953 --> 00:02:01.663
She brought in a full
bagel spread.

16
00:02:01.746 --> 00:02:03.456
- I'm just saying.
- She's not my replacement.

17
00:02:03.540 --> 00:02:04.999
She's just covering as chief
while I go

18
00:02:05.083 --> 00:02:06.376
- on my little sabbatical.
- Three months?

19
00:02:06.459 --> 00:02:07.919
I'll be back
before your daughter

20
00:02:08.002 --> 00:02:09.754
- sleeps through the night.
- Hey. dude. that's cold.

21
00:02:09.838 --> 00:02:11.506
- Morning.
- Good morning.

22
00:02:26.146 --> 00:02:27.689
Good morning. John.

23
00:02:27.772 --> 00:02:29.691
I could have sworn
it was still around 4:00 a.m..

24
00:02:29.774 --> 00:02:31.442
Did you guys have
an easy night last night?

25
00:02:31.526 --> 00:02:33.153
The waiting room
actually looks manageable.

26
00:02:33.236 --> 00:02:35.071
I wouldn't call it easy.
but not too bad.

27
00:02:35.155 --> 00:02:37.240
I figured we'd have hands
and burns down here a bunch.

28
00:02:37.323 --> 00:02:39.325
but so far nobody's
blown off any fingers.

29
00:02:39.409 --> 00:02:41.202
Oh. you know
you just jinxed it.

30
00:02:41.286 --> 00:02:42.579
You guys and your jinxes.

31
00:02:42.662 --> 00:02:45.290
- Please. Jesus. please.
- Hail Mary again.

32
00:02:45.373 --> 00:02:47.292
- In the sanctified flesh.
- Don't let me die alone.

33
00:02:47.375 --> 00:02:50.545
- Just try to relax. Margaret.
- I need a priest.

34
00:02:50.628 --> 00:02:53.214
- Hey. hey. Dr. Robby.
- What's the good word. Perlah?

35
00:02:53.298 --> 00:02:55.133
All your results came
back normal. Mrs. Walker.

36
00:02:55.216 --> 00:02:56.134
I'm dying.

37
00:02:56.217 --> 00:02:57.552
You're not dying.
Mrs. Walker. I promise.

38
00:02:57.635 --> 00:02:58.970
Jesus is coming for me.

39
00:02:59.053 --> 00:03:01.264
If He is. He hasn't checked
in at registration yet.

40
00:03:01.347 --> 00:03:02.599
Please don't let me die
a sinner.

41
00:03:02.682 --> 00:03:04.184
Don't worry. Margaret--
we're going to have

42
00:03:04.267 --> 00:03:06.144
the hospital chaplain come
and see you in a moment.

43
00:03:06.227 --> 00:03:07.645
I'm not going
to last that long.

44
00:03:07.729 --> 00:03:09.480
Yes. you will. because we're
going to give you a shot

45
00:03:09.564 --> 00:03:10.940
to keep you alive
until they get here.

46
00:03:11.024 --> 00:03:12.567
What are you thinking.
Dr. Robinavitch?

47
00:03:12.650 --> 00:03:14.444
500 mikes of cyanocobalamin?

48
00:03:14.527 --> 00:03:16.613
In her condition.
I'd push a full 1.000.

49
00:03:16.696 --> 00:03:19.657
Whoo.
You heard the man. Perlah.

50
00:03:19.741 --> 00:03:21.951
God bless you.
God bless all of you.

51
00:03:22.035 --> 00:03:23.536
Amen to that.

52
00:03:23.620 --> 00:03:25.538
Hail Mary. full of grace.
the Lord is with thee...

53
00:03:25.622 --> 00:03:27.373
Ooh. nothing like
the miracle healing powers

54
00:03:27.457 --> 00:03:28.875
of a good old B12 shot.

55
00:03:28.958 --> 00:03:32.003
- How does she hold down a job?
- She doesn't.

56
00:03:32.086 --> 00:03:33.671
She's wearing
a waitress uniform.

57
00:03:33.755 --> 00:03:35.256
Yeah. from a diner
that closed 20 years ago.

58
00:03:35.340 --> 00:03:37.550
Tier One Trauma.
ETA six minutes.

59
00:03:37.634 --> 00:03:39.385
And so it begins.

60
00:03:39.469 --> 00:03:41.846
My husband is still waiting
to see a doctor.

61
00:03:41.930 --> 00:03:43.139
I apologize for the wait.

62
00:03:43.223 --> 00:03:44.933
but here are two doctors
just for you.

63
00:03:45.016 --> 00:03:47.101
Mr. Burgess
has been complaining

64
00:03:47.185 --> 00:03:48.603
of leg cramps for a day.

65
00:03:48.686 --> 00:03:52.190
Slightly tachy at 110.
BP 128 over 75.

66
00:03:52.273 --> 00:03:54.150
Afebrile. good sats.

67
00:03:54.234 --> 00:03:56.110
I'm Dr. Shen.
but I'm going off shift.

68
00:03:56.194 --> 00:03:58.363
Dr. Robinavitch will be one of
the doctors looking after you.

69
00:03:58.446 --> 00:03:59.656
What other medications

70
00:03:59.739 --> 00:04:01.616
are you currently taking.
Mr. Burgess?

71
00:04:01.699 --> 00:04:03.701
I brought his meds.

72
00:04:03.785 --> 00:04:05.745
Thank you.

73
00:04:05.828 --> 00:04:07.288
These are his supplements.

74
00:04:07.372 --> 00:04:09.457
mostly all-natural and organic
where possible.

75
00:04:09.540 --> 00:04:12.210
And these are
his homeopathic prescriptions.

76
00:04:12.293 --> 00:04:16.297
I also have a list
of his refrigerated probiotics.

77
00:04:19.092 --> 00:04:20.969
Where the hell is everybody?

78
00:04:21.052 --> 00:04:23.221
Our new attending
is torturing

79
00:04:23.304 --> 00:04:25.473
our intern and med students
in Trauma One.

80
00:04:25.556 --> 00:04:27.767
She came in early
to meet the night shift

81
00:04:27.850 --> 00:04:29.352
and took things over.

82
00:04:29.435 --> 00:04:32.272
Okay. that takes giant balls
of disrespect.

83
00:04:32.355 --> 00:04:33.648
Giant Balls of Disrespect

84
00:04:33.731 --> 00:04:35.441
was the name
of my band in high school.

85
00:04:35.525 --> 00:04:37.652
And my nickname
for my ex-husband.

86
00:04:37.735 --> 00:04:39.821
Hey. uh.
is this your last shift?

87
00:04:39.904 --> 00:04:43.783
- For a while. yeah.
- Oh. I am so jealous.

88
00:04:43.866 --> 00:04:46.452
Hey. I'll pay you a grand
if you take my second husband.

89
00:04:46.536 --> 00:04:47.704
Tempting.

90
00:04:47.787 --> 00:04:49.664
So tell me about
this new attending.

91
00:04:49.747 --> 00:04:52.792
Uh. she's pretty.
divorced. one kid.

92
00:04:52.875 --> 00:04:55.336
Can already tell
she is a strict rule follower.

93
00:04:55.420 --> 00:04:57.255
I'm probably going
to grow to hate her.

94
00:04:57.338 --> 00:05:01.009
- What's her name. again?
- Dr. Baran Al-Hashimi.

95
00:05:01.092 --> 00:05:03.678
Al-Hashimi?
What is that?

96
00:05:03.761 --> 00:05:06.055
Irish?

97
00:05:06.139 --> 00:05:09.017
She's some sort
of clinical informatics expert.

98
00:05:09.100 --> 00:05:10.893
Once she started
talking about AI.

99
00:05:10.977 --> 00:05:14.272
I started thinking about robots
and kind of stopped listening.

100
00:05:14.355 --> 00:05:16.774
Clear.
Off the chest. Ogilvie.

101
00:05:16.858 --> 00:05:18.359
Get ready to step up here. Joy.

102
00:05:18.443 --> 00:05:20.611
Ogilvie. off the chest!

103
00:05:20.695 --> 00:05:22.071
Clear!

104
00:05:22.155 --> 00:05:23.906
Still V-tach.
but it looks weird.

105
00:05:23.990 --> 00:05:25.658
- Agreed.
- No pulse.

106
00:05:25.742 --> 00:05:27.785
No effusion.
good lung sliding.

107
00:05:27.869 --> 00:05:28.828
Start compressions. Joy.

108
00:05:28.911 --> 00:05:29.954
We haven't considered
all the Ts.

109
00:05:30.038 --> 00:05:31.956
I checked for tamponade
and tension pneumo.

110
00:05:32.040 --> 00:05:33.166
What if it's thrombosis?

111
00:05:33.249 --> 00:05:35.376
If it's a pulmonary or cardiac
clot. TNK could save him.

112
00:05:35.460 --> 00:05:37.462
We are sticking
with the algorithm for now.

113
00:05:37.545 --> 00:05:39.505
- Algorithm's not working.
- Faster and deeper. please.

114
00:05:39.589 --> 00:05:42.383
- Uh. you need a break. Joy?
- No. I need an attending.

115
00:05:42.467 --> 00:05:44.761
I'm right here.

116
00:05:44.844 --> 00:05:46.679
Stop compressions.
We're calling it.

117
00:05:48.222 --> 00:05:50.016
Sorry. the patient's dead.

118
00:05:52.894 --> 00:05:55.355
All right.
Who can tell me what went well?

119
00:05:55.438 --> 00:05:57.065
We followed
the V-tach algorithm.

120
00:05:57.148 --> 00:05:58.816
We checked
for reversible causes.

121
00:05:58.900 --> 00:06:00.568
We limited our rhythm
and pulse checks to 10 seconds.

122
00:06:00.651 --> 00:06:01.944
Excellent.

123
00:06:02.028 --> 00:06:03.237
Should we have
given thrombolytics?

124
00:06:03.321 --> 00:06:04.614
No. you should have
recognized

125
00:06:04.697 --> 00:06:06.741
that the cardiac rhythm
on the monitor was polymorphic.

126
00:06:06.824 --> 00:06:08.576
not just V-tach.

127
00:06:08.659 --> 00:06:10.495
It was torsades de pointes.

128
00:06:10.578 --> 00:06:12.747
That's French--
"twisting of the points."

129
00:06:12.830 --> 00:06:14.624
From prolonged QT.
antiarrhythmics.

130
00:06:14.707 --> 00:06:15.958
electrolyte disorders.

131
00:06:16.042 --> 00:06:17.210
Your patient would have lived

132
00:06:17.293 --> 00:06:18.920
if you had pushed
magnesium sulfate.

133
00:06:19.003 --> 00:06:20.797
Good news is
he's an organ donor.

134
00:06:20.880 --> 00:06:22.548
Parts of him are going to get
used to make Frisbees

135
00:06:22.632 --> 00:06:24.759
and water bottles and end up
as microplastics

136
00:06:24.842 --> 00:06:26.469
in our brains
and reproductive organs.

137
00:06:26.552 --> 00:06:28.137
Thank you for the words
of encouragement. boss.

138
00:06:28.221 --> 00:06:29.764
Dr. Al-Hashimi.
Dr. Michael Robinavitch.

139
00:06:29.847 --> 00:06:31.724
- Everybody calls me Robby.
- Baran. please.

140
00:06:31.808 --> 00:06:33.351
- Welcome to the Pitt.
- Yeah. about that--

141
00:06:33.434 --> 00:06:34.727
Trauma's a minute out.

142
00:06:34.811 --> 00:06:36.687
Ooh. who wants to treat
a real patient?

143
00:06:36.771 --> 00:06:38.106
Yes. please.

144
00:06:38.189 --> 00:06:40.024
This thing's going
to give me nightmares.

145
00:06:41.776 --> 00:06:43.736
I hope you don't mind me
jumping right into things.

146
00:06:43.820 --> 00:06:45.488
I find that a mock code
is a great way

147
00:06:45.571 --> 00:06:47.240
to assess
the students' capabilities.

148
00:06:47.323 --> 00:06:49.826
Well. it might have been nice
if we'd had a little time

149
00:06:49.909 --> 00:06:51.577
to go over how we do things.

150
00:06:51.661 --> 00:06:54.580
Did you not get a packet
from Dr. Underwood? Gloria?

151
00:06:54.664 --> 00:06:56.666
It outlined
the quality-improvement changes

152
00:06:56.749 --> 00:06:58.501
I instituted at the VA.

153
00:06:58.584 --> 00:06:59.794
We're adopting the program

154
00:06:59.877 --> 00:07:01.587
at all
of the university hospitals.

155
00:07:01.671 --> 00:07:03.965
- You didn't read it?
- No. I did. I mean. I will.

156
00:07:04.048 --> 00:07:05.508
I'm going to.
I want to.

157
00:07:05.591 --> 00:07:07.176
I thought I had
a little bit more time

158
00:07:07.260 --> 00:07:09.137
- before you came in today.
- We've already distributed

159
00:07:09.220 --> 00:07:11.639
patient passports
to everyone at registration.

160
00:07:11.722 --> 00:07:14.183
What is a patient passport?

161
00:07:14.267 --> 00:07:16.727
So glad you asked.

162
00:07:16.811 --> 00:07:18.604
- Samira?
- Dr. Al.

163
00:07:18.688 --> 00:07:21.232
We worked together
at the VA a few years ago.

164
00:07:21.315 --> 00:07:23.192
- And now you're an R4.
- Yes.

165
00:07:23.276 --> 00:07:25.278
And I'm so excited
you're joining us.

166
00:07:25.361 --> 00:07:26.737
Dr. Mel King is here. too.

167
00:07:26.821 --> 00:07:28.156
I think you worked
with her as well.

168
00:07:28.239 --> 00:07:29.866
- Incoming!
- I did indeed.

169
00:07:29.949 --> 00:07:31.826
John Doe--dishwasher.
penetrating trauma

170
00:07:31.909 --> 00:07:33.828
from a kitchen knife
to the right chest.

171
00:07:33.911 --> 00:07:35.288
- Assault or accident?
- Unclear.

172
00:07:35.371 --> 00:07:37.999
Initially had a pulse.
lost it two blocks away.

173
00:07:40.460 --> 00:07:42.420
What do we got. party people?

174
00:07:42.503 --> 00:07:45.631
Dr. Yolanda Garcia.
trauma surgery fellow.

175
00:07:45.715 --> 00:07:48.509
meet Dr. Baran Al-Hashimi.
new E.D. attending.

176
00:07:48.593 --> 00:07:50.386
She's gonna be covering for me
while I'm gone.

177
00:07:50.470 --> 00:07:51.929
So nice to meet you.

178
00:07:52.013 --> 00:07:53.431
About time they replaced you.
Rabbit-bitch.

179
00:07:53.514 --> 00:07:55.224
I'm gonna miss you.
too. Yolo.

180
00:07:55.308 --> 00:07:57.560
Dr. Garcia has a hard time
expressing her feelings.

181
00:07:57.643 --> 00:07:58.603
Not all of them.

182
00:07:58.686 --> 00:08:02.106
One. two. three.

183
00:08:02.190 --> 00:08:05.443
- Prep for a left thoracotomy.
- I'm on it.

184
00:08:05.526 --> 00:08:07.653
What's up. White Chocolate?

185
00:08:07.737 --> 00:08:11.491
Did you know our farm boy here
is a vintage-funk freak?

186
00:08:11.574 --> 00:08:13.868
Unfortunately.
he also likes to use

187
00:08:13.951 --> 00:08:16.412
- other people's toothbrushes.
- It was one time.

188
00:08:16.496 --> 00:08:18.039
They were the same color.

189
00:08:18.122 --> 00:08:20.041
- What's your plan. Samira?
- Dr. Mohan. next steps?

190
00:08:20.124 --> 00:08:21.375
Chest tube to the right.

191
00:08:21.459 --> 00:08:23.127
Stand by with massive
transfusion protocol.

192
00:08:23.211 --> 00:08:24.420
I put two units
on the infuser.

193
00:08:24.504 --> 00:08:25.755
Sterile gloves. 6 1/2.

194
00:08:25.838 --> 00:08:26.839
Here. we let the fellows

195
00:08:26.923 --> 00:08:28.257
and the residents
kind of take charge.

196
00:08:28.341 --> 00:08:30.426
I'll hold on to them
just in case.

197
00:08:30.510 --> 00:08:33.429
Is the VA even
a trauma center?

198
00:08:33.513 --> 00:08:37.016
Not for medic runs.
but they walk in--

199
00:08:37.099 --> 00:08:41.062
falls. major MVCs. GSWs.

200
00:08:41.145 --> 00:08:42.563
Stab wound's on the right.

201
00:08:42.647 --> 00:08:44.148
Why are we opening
the left chest?

202
00:08:44.232 --> 00:08:46.067
Better access
if it's tamponade.

203
00:08:46.150 --> 00:08:47.985
and you can cross-clamp
the aorta.

204
00:08:48.069 --> 00:08:49.612
Javadi. Whitaker.
sterile gloves.

205
00:08:49.695 --> 00:08:50.696
Can I glove up?

206
00:08:50.780 --> 00:08:53.282
It's best if you
watch the first one.

207
00:08:53.366 --> 00:08:55.034
This guy's dead anyway.

208
00:08:57.036 --> 00:09:00.081
- 10 blade.
- 28 French on a long Kelly.

209
00:09:01.290 --> 00:09:02.750
Javadi. you're on suction.

210
00:09:02.833 --> 00:09:05.670
Whitaker. get ready
for internal compressions.

211
00:09:07.547 --> 00:09:09.423
Sorry. that's my phone.

212
00:09:11.050 --> 00:09:12.510
Finochietto retractor.

213
00:09:12.593 --> 00:09:13.844
Whitaker.
give me a little room.

214
00:09:13.928 --> 00:09:15.096
I need to get to his heart.

215
00:09:15.179 --> 00:09:16.722
I'm in.
Hook up the Thora-Seal.

216
00:09:18.224 --> 00:09:19.433
You want me
to get that for you?

217
00:09:19.517 --> 00:09:21.602
Not right now.

218
00:09:29.986 --> 00:09:32.029
No tamponade.
pretty dry in here.

219
00:09:33.656 --> 00:09:35.157
Heart's empty.

220
00:09:35.241 --> 00:09:36.784
Somebody start cardiac massage.
I'll cross-clamp.

221
00:09:36.867 --> 00:09:37.952
Yeah. I got it.

222
00:09:38.035 --> 00:09:39.370
You do these one-handed.

223
00:09:39.453 --> 00:09:41.414
pushing up against the
breastbone with four fingers.

224
00:09:41.497 --> 00:09:43.374
- Very good.
- Not much blood to suction.

225
00:09:43.457 --> 00:09:45.960
- Okay. team. I think we need--
- Samira. next steps?

226
00:09:46.043 --> 00:09:47.044
Keep transfusing.

227
00:09:47.128 --> 00:09:48.546
- Open the right chest.
- That is correct.

228
00:09:48.629 --> 00:09:50.339
Booties on. kids.
There will be blood.

229
00:09:52.800 --> 00:09:54.635
Frank?

230
00:09:56.178 --> 00:09:59.223
Langdon.

231
00:09:59.307 --> 00:10:01.392
Frank?

232
00:10:08.524 --> 00:10:10.568
You should be good
to go now. hon.

233
00:10:10.651 --> 00:10:12.695
- Thanks. Lupe.
- Of course.

234
00:10:12.778 --> 00:10:14.614
Hey. go get 'em.

235
00:10:17.617 --> 00:10:19.952
Hey. Doc.

236
00:10:20.036 --> 00:10:22.955
It's been a while.

237
00:10:23.039 --> 00:10:26.584
I got a-a bad toothache today.

238
00:10:26.667 --> 00:10:29.253
We'll take care
of that. Louie.

239
00:10:29.337 --> 00:10:30.671
All right.

240
00:11:04.038 --> 00:11:06.207
There's too much blood
to suction.

241
00:11:06.290 --> 00:11:08.209
Uh. retracting the lung.

242
00:11:08.292 --> 00:11:10.586
- Try to identify the source.
- Could be the right ventricle.

243
00:11:10.670 --> 00:11:12.546
Or more likely. the hilum.

244
00:11:12.630 --> 00:11:14.298
Fresh lap pads.

245
00:11:15.675 --> 00:11:18.969
Siri. turn on silent mode!

246
00:12:09.562 --> 00:12:11.063
Good morning.

247
00:12:11.147 --> 00:12:12.815
If it was a good morning.
I'd still be in bed.

248
00:12:12.898 --> 00:12:14.483
So what are you doing here?

249
00:12:14.567 --> 00:12:16.485
Benji's mom is visiting
for the holiday.

250
00:12:16.569 --> 00:12:18.487
- She's still alive?
- That woman's too mean to die.

251
00:12:18.571 --> 00:12:20.114
Plus. who else is going
to get this place

252
00:12:20.197 --> 00:12:21.907
through
the Fourth of July weekend?

253
00:12:21.991 --> 00:12:23.701
Sure as hell
ain't going to be me.

254
00:12:23.784 --> 00:12:26.036
I rest my case.
What am I walking into?

255
00:12:26.120 --> 00:12:27.621
Nothing too bad. yet.

256
00:12:27.705 --> 00:12:29.832
Uh. these are the ones
I'd keep an eye on.

257
00:12:31.751 --> 00:12:34.628
The prodigal son returns.

258
00:12:34.712 --> 00:12:35.796
Too soon?

259
00:12:35.880 --> 00:12:38.257
No. I guess not.

260
00:12:38.340 --> 00:12:40.926
- You're back.
- I took some time.

261
00:12:41.010 --> 00:12:44.138
I'm like an old trail horse--
I always find my way back home.

262
00:12:44.221 --> 00:12:45.890
You look good. kid.
How you feeling?

263
00:12:45.973 --> 00:12:47.850
Uh. yeah. great.

264
00:12:47.933 --> 00:12:50.436
You know. it's been a...

265
00:12:50.519 --> 00:12:52.938
- it's been a journey.
- I bet.

266
00:12:53.022 --> 00:12:54.607
Thanks.
Robby around?

267
00:12:54.690 --> 00:12:56.525
Uh. he's in with a trauma.

268
00:12:56.609 --> 00:12:58.944
But if you hurry back. you can
catch some of the pass-ons.

269
00:12:59.028 --> 00:13:01.238
- They're in North.
- Uh. thanks.

270
00:13:03.032 --> 00:13:05.034
I'll keep an eye on him.

271
00:13:07.161 --> 00:13:09.371
I think we have
a lost little lamb.

272
00:13:09.455 --> 00:13:11.999
Uh. excuse me. hon.
Can we help you?

273
00:13:12.082 --> 00:13:13.959
I'm looking
for the charge nurse.

274
00:13:14.043 --> 00:13:16.045
Oh. well.
you found two of 'em.

275
00:13:16.128 --> 00:13:17.463
I'm Lena.
This is Dana.

276
00:13:17.546 --> 00:13:18.756
I'm night shift. going home.

277
00:13:18.839 --> 00:13:21.091
but Dana is queen
of the day shift.

278
00:13:21.175 --> 00:13:23.177
Emma Nolan.
Nice to meet you both.

279
00:13:23.260 --> 00:13:25.638
Uh. I'm a new grad RN
here to shadow.

280
00:13:25.721 --> 00:13:27.181
Welcome to the Pitt.
Emma Nolan.

281
00:13:27.264 --> 00:13:28.891
Here. let me put some
of your stuff behind the desk.

282
00:13:28.974 --> 00:13:31.685
- and I'll give you a quick tour.
- Okay.

283
00:13:31.769 --> 00:13:34.188
- Where you from. sweetheart?
- Sault Ste. Marie.

284
00:13:34.271 --> 00:13:35.648
Oh.

285
00:13:35.731 --> 00:13:38.192
It's in Upper Michigan.
practically Canada.

286
00:13:38.275 --> 00:13:41.028
My great-grandmother
was from up that way--

287
00:13:41.111 --> 00:13:44.198
nice area. a lot of bugs.

288
00:13:44.281 --> 00:13:46.033
How about a cup of coffee?

289
00:13:47.493 --> 00:13:48.994
Can't locate the source.

290
00:13:49.078 --> 00:13:50.788
Proximal hilum
is under the sternum.

291
00:13:50.871 --> 00:13:52.790
Along with most
of the right ventricle.

292
00:13:52.873 --> 00:13:55.584
- You need better exposure.
- Convert to a clamshell.

293
00:13:55.668 --> 00:13:58.003
- Exactly.
- Trauma shears.

294
00:13:58.087 --> 00:14:00.631
Would've been nice to let
them come up with that plan.

295
00:14:00.714 --> 00:14:02.716
Heart's going to need double
compressions just like this.

296
00:14:04.176 --> 00:14:06.554
Squeeze from the apex
to the aorta.

297
00:14:08.180 --> 00:14:09.723
Right ventricle looks good.

298
00:14:09.807 --> 00:14:11.141
Massive hemorrhage
from the hilum.

299
00:14:11.225 --> 00:14:14.687
Second MTP pack is going.
additional four units.

300
00:14:14.770 --> 00:14:17.106
Hilar injury
looks very proximal--

301
00:14:17.189 --> 00:14:19.316
may be pulmonary artery
and vein.

302
00:14:19.400 --> 00:14:22.027
Clamp's on.
Nope. no good.

303
00:14:22.111 --> 00:14:23.529
Still bleeding
like a stuck pig.

304
00:14:23.612 --> 00:14:24.530
I can give it a try.

305
00:14:24.613 --> 00:14:25.906
Dr. Garcia is
a very skilled surgeon.

306
00:14:25.990 --> 00:14:27.575
If she can't get it. we need
to think of something else.

307
00:14:27.658 --> 00:14:28.826
Like what?

308
00:14:32.329 --> 00:14:33.747
Hilar flip.

309
00:14:33.831 --> 00:14:35.416
We're going to rotate
the lung 180 degrees.

310
00:14:35.499 --> 00:14:37.042
like putting a kink
in the garden hose.

311
00:14:37.126 --> 00:14:39.795
- It'll stop the bleeding.
- That could possibly work.

312
00:14:39.879 --> 00:14:43.549
Or he'll die when you rip
the entire lung off the hilum.

313
00:14:43.632 --> 00:14:46.385
Gently. very. very gently.
very. very slowly.

314
00:15:02.109 --> 00:15:03.861
- Blood loss is slowing down.
- That's a good sign.

315
00:15:03.944 --> 00:15:05.154
Hilum looks dry.

316
00:15:05.237 --> 00:15:06.989
Yeah. but the heart
feels empty.

317
00:15:07.072 --> 00:15:09.533
Okay. we fixed the leak.
Now let's fill the tank.

318
00:15:11.785 --> 00:15:13.787
You are very popular today.

319
00:15:13.871 --> 00:15:16.624
Sorry. I'll turn it off
when I can.

320
00:15:20.836 --> 00:15:22.463
Nine-year-old Kylie Connors--

321
00:15:22.546 --> 00:15:24.673
brought in by
her dad's girlfriend. Gina.

322
00:15:24.757 --> 00:15:27.092
Kylie took a tumble
on the stairs this morning.

323
00:15:27.176 --> 00:15:30.054
3-centimeter chin lac
and a chipped front incisor.

324
00:15:30.137 --> 00:15:32.014
She's got LET
on a pressure dressing.

325
00:15:32.097 --> 00:15:33.849
Bleeding pretty good
on arrival.

326
00:15:33.933 --> 00:15:36.018
Dermabond should do the trick.

327
00:15:36.101 --> 00:15:38.062
Any questions?

328
00:15:38.145 --> 00:15:40.481
Dr. King?

329
00:15:40.564 --> 00:15:41.899
Mel?

330
00:15:41.982 --> 00:15:44.568
Oh. um.
I didn't say anything.

331
00:15:47.404 --> 00:15:50.115
- Uh. how you feeling. Kylie?
- Tired.

332
00:15:50.199 --> 00:15:52.910
- We've been here since 5:30.
- Oh. that makes two of us.

333
00:15:52.993 --> 00:15:55.287
But don't worry.
We'll patch you up good as new.

334
00:15:55.371 --> 00:15:57.915
And we will get you out of here
as soon as we can.

335
00:15:57.998 --> 00:15:59.333
- Any questions?
- Can you raise your chin?

336
00:15:59.416 --> 00:16:01.210
No. I'm just
her dad's girlfriend.

337
00:16:01.293 --> 00:16:03.253
- so I'm new to all this.
- No worries. We got you.

338
00:16:03.337 --> 00:16:04.588
Next.

339
00:16:06.215 --> 00:16:10.010
26-year-old Liam Sanders--
took a fall from his bicycle.

340
00:16:10.094 --> 00:16:12.137
No LOC. nonfocal neuro.

341
00:16:12.221 --> 00:16:14.431
lower-leg lac
with no bony tenderness.

342
00:16:14.515 --> 00:16:16.266
Were you wearing
a helmet. Liam?

343
00:16:16.350 --> 00:16:18.185
No. I was just riding
in my neighborhood.

344
00:16:18.268 --> 00:16:19.937
You should always
wear a helmet.

345
00:16:20.020 --> 00:16:21.438
Hey. nice of you to join us.

346
00:16:21.522 --> 00:16:23.607
- Hey.
- Dr. Langdon!

347
00:16:26.068 --> 00:16:28.779
Sold to Dr. Langdon.

348
00:16:28.862 --> 00:16:31.115
Candace O'Grady. 82...

349
00:16:31.198 --> 00:16:35.369
Brought in by her son Richard
for intractable vomiting.

350
00:16:37.246 --> 00:16:38.956
Hardly any hemorrhage
on the right.

351
00:16:39.039 --> 00:16:40.416
- Looks like the flip worked.
- How's the heart. Whitaker?

352
00:16:40.499 --> 00:16:42.376
Feels full of blood.
First time since we started.

353
00:16:42.459 --> 00:16:46.296
Hold compressions.

354
00:16:46.380 --> 00:16:48.966
- Quivering bag of worms.
- Resume compressions.

355
00:16:49.049 --> 00:16:51.468
When the heart quivers
like that. it's obvious V-fib.

356
00:16:51.552 --> 00:16:54.763
- Okay. internal paddles ready.
- Mm-hmm. Charge to...?

357
00:16:54.847 --> 00:16:56.557
- 25 joules.
- 50 joules.

358
00:16:56.640 --> 00:16:58.475
50 gets it right
the first time.

359
00:16:58.559 --> 00:17:00.644
Charged.

360
00:17:00.728 --> 00:17:01.937
Okay. Whitaker.
when you're ready.

361
00:17:02.021 --> 00:17:04.023
Clear.

362
00:17:06.650 --> 00:17:08.736
That's what normal sinus
looks like.

363
00:17:10.571 --> 00:17:11.572
Strong carotid.

364
00:17:11.655 --> 00:17:14.700
Saline lap pads
and up to the OR.

365
00:17:14.783 --> 00:17:16.994
That's a hell of a way
to start the day.

366
00:17:17.077 --> 00:17:20.831
Unconventional.
but a decent outcome.

367
00:17:20.914 --> 00:17:23.167
Why don't we split up
for efficiency?

368
00:17:23.250 --> 00:17:25.586
Residents present to either
one of us but not both.

369
00:17:27.087 --> 00:17:29.048
We can certainly
discuss that.

370
00:17:33.552 --> 00:17:35.429
Were you feeling weak
or dizzy?

371
00:17:35.512 --> 00:17:36.805
No.

372
00:17:36.889 --> 00:17:38.515
I-I got up to pee.
and I tripped over

373
00:17:38.599 --> 00:17:40.559
a laundry basket that
I couldn't see in the dark.

374
00:17:40.642 --> 00:17:42.102
Did you hit your head?

375
00:17:42.186 --> 00:17:44.021
Does my chart say
that I hit my head?

376
00:17:44.104 --> 00:17:46.231
No. we just
want to be thorough

377
00:17:46.315 --> 00:17:48.484
to make sure
you don't miss anything.

378
00:17:48.567 --> 00:17:50.819
How about we focus
on patching me up?

379
00:17:50.903 --> 00:17:52.446
Ah!

380
00:17:52.529 --> 00:17:54.448
All right. Mr. Williams.

381
00:17:54.531 --> 00:17:56.241
we're going to check an X-ray
of your wrist

382
00:17:56.325 --> 00:17:58.452
and try to get you out of here
as quickly as possible.

383
00:17:58.535 --> 00:18:00.954
Great. And let's keep
the bullshit extra charges

384
00:18:01.038 --> 00:18:02.456
to a minimum. huh?

385
00:18:02.539 --> 00:18:04.750
My deductible
is already a bitch.

386
00:18:07.336 --> 00:18:09.129
Sure.

387
00:18:30.859 --> 00:18:32.194
Bye.

388
00:18:32.277 --> 00:18:34.655
My mother is trying
to destroy my life.

389
00:18:34.738 --> 00:18:36.824
Yeah. they seem
to take pleasure in that.

390
00:18:36.907 --> 00:18:38.659
I committed
to a partnership-track position

391
00:18:38.742 --> 00:18:40.494
next year at a hospital
back in Jersey

392
00:18:40.577 --> 00:18:42.496
so I could be close
and support her.

393
00:18:42.579 --> 00:18:45.499
But now she's getting married
and selling our house

394
00:18:45.582 --> 00:18:48.043
to go on a year-long cruise
around the world.

395
00:18:48.127 --> 00:18:50.629
Wow.
I mean. that's a--

396
00:18:50.712 --> 00:18:52.589
Pretty fucking stupid idea.
if you ask me.

397
00:18:52.673 --> 00:18:54.675
She's known this guy
less than a year.

398
00:18:54.758 --> 00:18:58.053
What if he's a player?
What if she disappears at sea?

399
00:18:58.137 --> 00:18:59.805
I mean.
what if they're in love?

400
00:18:59.888 --> 00:19:01.473
Lust is more like it.

401
00:19:01.557 --> 00:19:04.601
That is even better.

402
00:19:04.685 --> 00:19:07.896
Man. it has been a while.

403
00:19:07.980 --> 00:19:11.316
and I'm solo this weekend.

404
00:19:11.400 --> 00:19:13.610
I need to get laid.

405
00:19:17.531 --> 00:19:19.575
It's a little much
before 8:00 a.m.. right?

406
00:19:19.658 --> 00:19:21.451
Yeah.

407
00:19:22.995 --> 00:19:24.746
Or ever.

408
00:19:30.210 --> 00:19:31.712
How's it going. Esme?

409
00:19:31.795 --> 00:19:34.006
Oh. just another day
in paradise.

410
00:19:51.231 --> 00:19:53.901
Heard you're going on a trip.

411
00:19:53.984 --> 00:19:56.153
Taking a sabbatical.
Leave tonight.

412
00:19:56.236 --> 00:19:57.988
Where you going?

413
00:19:58.071 --> 00:20:01.825
Um. Head-Smashed-In
Buffalo Jump.

414
00:20:01.909 --> 00:20:04.620
Captain Crunch
flying squirrel socks.

415
00:20:04.703 --> 00:20:07.915
What. are we talking in code.
or are you having a stroke?

416
00:20:07.998 --> 00:20:11.376
It's an Aboriginal UNESCO
Heritage Site in Alberta.

417
00:20:11.460 --> 00:20:13.378
I've never seen the Badlands.

418
00:20:13.462 --> 00:20:16.590
What is this. like. uh.
some sort of spirit quest?

419
00:20:16.673 --> 00:20:19.885
Uh. yeah.
something like that.

420
00:20:19.968 --> 00:20:22.512
Look. I. uh--
I guess we should talk.

421
00:20:22.596 --> 00:20:24.848
- Got a lot of things I need to--
- At some point. not right now.

422
00:20:24.932 --> 00:20:26.516
Right now
I got to hit the head.

423
00:20:26.600 --> 00:20:28.518
and I would like you to go
help Donnie out in Triage.

424
00:20:28.602 --> 00:20:29.895
Triage?

425
00:20:29.978 --> 00:20:31.438
N-no.

426
00:20:31.521 --> 00:20:33.148
No. I already picked up
a patient in North 2.

427
00:20:33.232 --> 00:20:34.566
a bicycle fall leg lac.
so maybe--

428
00:20:34.650 --> 00:20:35.692
Pretty sure
we can cover for you.

429
00:20:35.776 --> 00:20:38.987
We've been doing it for months.

430
00:20:39.071 --> 00:20:40.572
Right.

431
00:20:40.656 --> 00:20:43.158
No. and I--and I am--
I am very. uh--

432
00:20:43.242 --> 00:20:44.868
both very sorry
and appreciative of that.

433
00:20:44.952 --> 00:20:46.370
I just would hate to think

434
00:20:46.453 --> 00:20:49.039
that this is some kind
of a punishment for...

435
00:20:49.122 --> 00:20:50.999
but. uh. yeah.
Yeah. No. for sure.

436
00:20:51.083 --> 00:20:54.628
We'll--we'll talk later.
before you go.

437
00:20:54.711 --> 00:20:57.089
Like I said. not right now.

438
00:20:57.172 --> 00:20:59.466
Donnie just passed
his NP certification.

439
00:20:59.549 --> 00:21:01.426
He can help if you get in
over your head.

440
00:21:04.930 --> 00:21:06.807
Hey. Mel...

441
00:21:06.890 --> 00:21:09.685
can you take over
a bike fall leg lac in North 2

442
00:21:09.768 --> 00:21:11.561
for Langdon
while he's out in Triage?

443
00:21:11.645 --> 00:21:13.355
Um. you know. I-I can work
in Triage if you want--

444
00:21:13.438 --> 00:21:15.232
No. I want to keep Langdon
out in Triage.

445
00:21:15.315 --> 00:21:16.942
and I want to keep you
back here.

446
00:21:17.025 --> 00:21:19.444
- You okay with that?
- Sure.

447
00:21:19.528 --> 00:21:21.488
- Great.
- Absolutely.

448
00:21:27.536 --> 00:21:29.162
So...

449
00:21:29.246 --> 00:21:31.415
who should I pick up?

450
00:21:31.498 --> 00:21:33.458
We're about to get
the morning rush.

451
00:21:33.542 --> 00:21:34.668
What do you mean?

452
00:21:34.751 --> 00:21:36.169
Every morning
around this time.

453
00:21:36.253 --> 00:21:38.588
the nursing homes
and assisted-living facilities

454
00:21:38.672 --> 00:21:41.341
- do their morning bed checks.
- Uh-huh.

455
00:21:44.136 --> 00:21:46.638
It looks pretty quiet to me.

456
00:21:49.933 --> 00:21:52.060
Huh.

457
00:21:52.144 --> 00:21:53.770
Incoming.

458
00:21:53.854 --> 00:21:55.480
Oh. like I said.

459
00:21:55.564 --> 00:21:57.024
Come on.

460
00:21:57.107 --> 00:21:58.567
Ethan Bostick. 79--

461
00:21:58.650 --> 00:22:00.652
found altered this morning
at assisted living.

462
00:22:00.736 --> 00:22:01.987
No history of dementia.

463
00:22:02.070 --> 00:22:03.864
- Has a POLST.
- What's a POLST?

464
00:22:03.947 --> 00:22:06.491
Physician Orders
for Life-Sustaining Treatment--

465
00:22:06.575 --> 00:22:08.952
no CPR. no intubation.

466
00:22:09.036 --> 00:22:11.038
Then there's--
there's nothing for us to do.

467
00:22:11.121 --> 00:22:12.873
South 15 is open.

468
00:22:12.956 --> 00:22:15.876
Uh. well. "do not resuscitate"
does not mean "do not treat."

469
00:22:15.959 --> 00:22:20.047
He may perk up with fluids.
IV antibiotics.

470
00:22:24.593 --> 00:22:25.802
What's the good word. Crash?

471
00:22:25.886 --> 00:22:28.138
You save
that ventriloquist dummy?

472
00:22:28.221 --> 00:22:29.890
- Yeah.
- Really?

473
00:22:29.973 --> 00:22:32.309
No.

474
00:22:32.392 --> 00:22:34.311
Wait. tell me
you're not actually charting

475
00:22:34.394 --> 00:22:36.521
- about losing a mannequin.
- It's part of the exercise.

476
00:22:36.605 --> 00:22:38.315
Dr. Al-Hashimi
asked us to do it.

477
00:22:38.398 --> 00:22:40.317
Who's his next of kin--
Barbie?

478
00:22:41.985 --> 00:22:45.906
What's your. uh. take
on the new attending?

479
00:22:45.989 --> 00:22:47.616
Too soon to tell.

480
00:22:49.576 --> 00:22:50.827
You?

481
00:22:50.911 --> 00:22:52.120
She's already bugging me

482
00:22:52.204 --> 00:22:53.747
about being behind
on my charting.

483
00:22:53.830 --> 00:22:55.415
Now I know why everyone says

484
00:22:55.499 --> 00:22:57.667
being a second-year resident
sucks--because it does.

485
00:22:57.751 --> 00:22:59.503
I must've slept through
the part of med school

486
00:22:59.586 --> 00:23:02.339
where they tell you 90% of
your time will be spent typing.

487
00:23:02.422 --> 00:23:03.924
Which is just one more reason

488
00:23:04.007 --> 00:23:06.134
surgery is
a better lifestyle choice.

489
00:23:06.218 --> 00:23:09.137
Hey. Dr. Shamsi.
Dr. Trinity Santos.

490
00:23:09.221 --> 00:23:11.348
Ah. yes. the ER intern
who's interested

491
00:23:11.431 --> 00:23:13.350
- in my surgery program.
- That's me.

492
00:23:13.433 --> 00:23:15.936
But I'm an R2 now and thinking
of double boarding

493
00:23:16.019 --> 00:23:17.771
in surgery
and emergency medicine.

494
00:23:17.854 --> 00:23:20.273
which I know would sound
ridiculously ambitious

495
00:23:20.357 --> 00:23:22.609
if I didn't have the talent
to back it up.

496
00:23:22.692 --> 00:23:24.236
And the required attitude.

497
00:23:25.904 --> 00:23:27.572
Are you here to see a patient?

498
00:23:27.656 --> 00:23:29.366
I was. I did.

499
00:23:29.449 --> 00:23:30.742
And now I'm here to learn

500
00:23:30.826 --> 00:23:33.370
why you aren't returning
my calls or texts.

501
00:23:33.453 --> 00:23:34.955
Okay. I'm out.

502
00:23:35.038 --> 00:23:37.040
Nice seeing you again.
Dr. Shamsi.

503
00:23:37.124 --> 00:23:38.625
As soon as I get
a little free time.

504
00:23:38.708 --> 00:23:40.710
I will make plans for all of us
to do something together.

505
00:23:40.794 --> 00:23:42.587
- What about Tuesday?
- I'm working.

506
00:23:42.671 --> 00:23:44.464
On your birthday?

507
00:23:44.548 --> 00:23:46.216
I will call you
and Dad tomorrow.

508
00:23:46.299 --> 00:23:47.968
and we'll come up with something
to do together. I promise.

509
00:23:48.051 --> 00:23:49.970
But right now I actually have

510
00:23:50.053 --> 00:23:52.264
a bunch
of night-shift hand-offs.

511
00:23:59.396 --> 00:24:03.066
We have schedules.
You have chaos.

512
00:24:03.150 --> 00:24:05.193
You know she's wasting
her talents down here.

513
00:24:05.277 --> 00:24:08.196
Victoria is a big girl.
She can make her own decisions.

514
00:24:08.280 --> 00:24:11.783
She's also a young girl who's
still very impressionable.

515
00:24:11.867 --> 00:24:14.828
- And you can be very...
- "Pressionable"?

516
00:24:17.497 --> 00:24:18.790
Yes?

517
00:24:18.874 --> 00:24:20.167
Who?

518
00:24:20.250 --> 00:24:21.626
Who?

519
00:24:21.710 --> 00:24:24.421
Oh. for God's sake.
I'll be right there.

520
00:24:24.504 --> 00:24:26.923
We need to talk.

521
00:24:27.007 --> 00:24:29.301
How about same time tomorrow?

522
00:24:31.928 --> 00:24:33.680
Next Tuesday's your birthday?

523
00:24:33.763 --> 00:24:35.932
No.

524
00:24:36.016 --> 00:24:38.226
- Yes.
- Your 21st birthday?

525
00:24:38.310 --> 00:24:39.644
Please don't
say anything. okay?

526
00:24:39.728 --> 00:24:41.021
I-I get a little anxious
about--

527
00:24:41.104 --> 00:24:42.522
Dr. Santos. little girl
with the chin lac

528
00:24:42.606 --> 00:24:44.024
is getting into a gown.

529
00:24:44.107 --> 00:24:46.651
Don't want anyone to know what?

530
00:24:46.735 --> 00:24:48.945
Nothing.

531
00:24:49.029 --> 00:24:51.156
- Have a good day.
- You too.

532
00:24:52.908 --> 00:24:53.950
Oh.

533
00:24:55.368 --> 00:24:58.038
Hey. Duke. I'm just calling
to remind you

534
00:24:58.121 --> 00:25:01.041
that this is my last shift
for a while.

535
00:25:01.124 --> 00:25:03.585
So I need you to come in
before 3:00

536
00:25:03.668 --> 00:25:07.047
in case we need
to run some tests.

537
00:25:07.130 --> 00:25:09.758
Okay?
We had a deal. brother.

538
00:25:11.843 --> 00:25:13.887
- Oh. Hello.
- Hi.

539
00:25:13.970 --> 00:25:16.056
- I know you're crazy busy.
- Always.

540
00:25:16.139 --> 00:25:18.141
But I figured we should
really go over a few things

541
00:25:18.225 --> 00:25:19.684
- before you're gone.
- Sure.

542
00:25:19.768 --> 00:25:21.770
Where would you like to start?

543
00:25:21.853 --> 00:25:23.480
Well. one little thing
that I think

544
00:25:23.563 --> 00:25:26.066
would have a big impact
with staff and patients alike

545
00:25:26.149 --> 00:25:27.901
is if we launched a campaign

546
00:25:27.984 --> 00:25:31.071
to eradicate referring
to this wonderful department

547
00:25:31.154 --> 00:25:33.698
- as the Pitt.
- Really?

548
00:25:33.782 --> 00:25:35.700
I know you think
it's silly and petty.

549
00:25:35.784 --> 00:25:37.702
No. I think it's
just kind of endearing.

550
00:25:37.786 --> 00:25:41.581
- pretty damn accurate.
- I would argue the opposite.

551
00:25:41.665 --> 00:25:44.084
I think subconsciously
it affects those who work here.

552
00:25:44.167 --> 00:25:45.710
It also lowers expectations.

553
00:25:45.794 --> 00:25:48.088
which in turn lowers
patient-satisfaction scores.

554
00:25:48.171 --> 00:25:49.923
You have been talking
to Gloria.

555
00:25:50.006 --> 00:25:53.343
- Yes. and she agrees with me.
- Don't doubt that for a moment.

556
00:25:53.426 --> 00:25:55.220
You have to see the man
over there right now!

557
00:25:55.303 --> 00:25:57.806
We see people in order
of severity. ma'am.

558
00:26:01.268 --> 00:26:02.686
I don't know
what you're saying.

559
00:26:02.769 --> 00:26:05.021
I can taste the shit
in the back of my throat.

560
00:26:05.105 --> 00:26:06.314
Actually. the lady's right.

561
00:26:06.398 --> 00:26:07.941
He's going to make
all of us sick.

562
00:26:08.024 --> 00:26:09.025
Yes. please.

563
00:26:15.907 --> 00:26:17.409
All right.

564
00:26:17.492 --> 00:26:18.952
We'll get him back.

565
00:26:19.035 --> 00:26:21.371
Tell Dana
we're bringing the funk.

566
00:26:21.454 --> 00:26:23.456
- Oh. my God.
- Whew!

567
00:26:24.332 --> 00:26:26.751
So when did your eye start
bothering you. Ms. Mathews?

568
00:26:26.835 --> 00:26:28.795
Sister Grace. please.

569
00:26:28.878 --> 00:26:30.839
I'm only married to God.

570
00:26:30.922 --> 00:26:32.549
Of course. I'm sorry.

571
00:26:32.632 --> 00:26:36.136
A few days ago.
I thought it was pink eye

572
00:26:36.219 --> 00:26:38.346
or maybe I scratched it
while gardening.

573
00:26:38.430 --> 00:26:40.557
It's a very bad case
of conjunctivitis.

574
00:26:40.640 --> 00:26:42.350
We should send a sample
to the lab

575
00:26:42.434 --> 00:26:43.810
to direct our treatment.

576
00:26:43.893 --> 00:26:45.729
Look up for me.
Thank you.

577
00:26:48.982 --> 00:26:51.776
Okay. I'll put a numbing drop
in your eye

578
00:26:51.860 --> 00:26:54.863
and check for a scratch
with a special lamp.

579
00:26:57.866 --> 00:26:59.784
And I'll get you
to look up for me again.

580
00:26:59.868 --> 00:27:01.578
Thank you.

581
00:27:01.661 --> 00:27:04.080
Have you ever considered
serving God?

582
00:27:04.164 --> 00:27:05.248
Which one?

583
00:27:05.332 --> 00:27:07.584
Excuse me?

584
00:27:07.667 --> 00:27:09.377
My family is Hindu.

585
00:27:09.461 --> 00:27:12.172
so we have. like.
33 different kinds of deities.

586
00:27:12.255 --> 00:27:14.424
Oh. we have the one.

587
00:27:14.507 --> 00:27:17.469
Some people
only need one. right?

588
00:27:17.552 --> 00:27:18.970
Okay.

589
00:27:21.181 --> 00:27:23.975
Most important rule
around here--be smart. be safe.

590
00:27:24.059 --> 00:27:26.019
I can't warn you enough
about protecting yourself

591
00:27:26.102 --> 00:27:27.437
and your fellow nurses.

592
00:27:27.520 --> 00:27:29.898
We use the STAMP acronym
to assess patients.

593
00:27:29.981 --> 00:27:31.316
You know it?

594
00:27:31.399 --> 00:27:33.860
Uh. S is for staring
or refusal to make eye contact.

595
00:27:33.943 --> 00:27:35.528
If they're staring.
they're scaring.

596
00:27:35.612 --> 00:27:37.072
- T?
- Tone of voice.

597
00:27:37.155 --> 00:27:39.449
Often the threat level
rises with their voice.

598
00:27:39.532 --> 00:27:40.909
A is for anxiety.

599
00:27:40.992 --> 00:27:42.577
You can also think
"aggression."

600
00:27:42.661 --> 00:27:43.953
M is mumbling.

601
00:27:44.037 --> 00:27:45.205
Which. if you
listen closely enough.

602
00:27:45.288 --> 00:27:46.873
is often them saying
what they're thinking of doing

603
00:27:46.956 --> 00:27:48.541
as they talk themselves
up to it.

604
00:27:48.625 --> 00:27:50.085
- And P?
- Pacing.

605
00:27:50.168 --> 00:27:51.461
Good.

606
00:27:51.544 --> 00:27:53.421
We also have a safe word--
"hula hoop."

607
00:27:53.505 --> 00:27:55.215
I guess technically
it's two words. but whatever.

608
00:27:55.298 --> 00:27:57.217
If there's a threat.
say "hula hoop."

609
00:27:57.300 --> 00:28:00.637
and we'll all respond.

610
00:28:00.720 --> 00:28:02.222
Yeah?

611
00:28:02.305 --> 00:28:03.682
Lovely.

612
00:28:03.765 --> 00:28:07.852
Okay. I'll be right there
with reinforcements.

613
00:28:07.936 --> 00:28:10.730
Duty calls.
We're headed for Triage.

614
00:28:16.528 --> 00:28:18.405
We're going to get
your cast off--

615
00:28:37.549 --> 00:28:40.176
The antibiotics
should clear everything up.

616
00:28:40.260 --> 00:28:43.096
but you should try to stay
off it for a few days.

617
00:28:43.179 --> 00:28:46.474
Uh. I have to work.
I'm late as it is.

618
00:28:46.558 --> 00:28:50.478
Well. um. take breaks
and elevate when you can.

619
00:28:50.562 --> 00:28:52.313
Tylenol and Advil for the pain.

620
00:28:52.397 --> 00:28:55.066
If the pain persists or feel
like it's getting worse.

621
00:28:55.150 --> 00:28:56.276
come on back.

622
00:28:56.359 --> 00:28:58.611
- We'll get you fixed up.
- Thanks.

623
00:28:58.695 --> 00:29:01.656
They said give this
to the doctor.

624
00:29:01.740 --> 00:29:04.701
- What the hell is it?
- Patient passport.

625
00:29:04.784 --> 00:29:06.703
Lets patients know
what they're waiting for

626
00:29:06.786 --> 00:29:08.204
and how long it'll take.

627
00:29:08.288 --> 00:29:10.498
You check off if he needs labs.
X-rays. CT.

628
00:29:10.582 --> 00:29:12.459
None of the above.
When did we start this?

629
00:29:12.542 --> 00:29:14.502
Today. the new attending.

630
00:29:16.337 --> 00:29:18.590
What's up
with your tooth. Louie?

631
00:29:18.673 --> 00:29:21.301
It's been going on
for a while.

632
00:29:21.384 --> 00:29:23.303
but it got bad last night.

633
00:29:23.386 --> 00:29:25.930
Lower-left side.

634
00:29:26.014 --> 00:29:28.099
Okay.

635
00:29:28.183 --> 00:29:31.561
Oh. yeah.

636
00:29:31.644 --> 00:29:33.438
It could be an infection
at the root.

637
00:29:33.521 --> 00:29:36.608
We can drain it. but then...

638
00:29:36.691 --> 00:29:38.777
you're. uh--you're breathing
kind of fast.

639
00:29:38.860 --> 00:29:40.695
Yeah. I've been--

640
00:29:40.779 --> 00:29:44.157
well. I've been.
uh. walking more.

641
00:29:44.240 --> 00:29:45.825
trying to get in shape.

642
00:29:45.909 --> 00:29:48.661
But sometimes I get
a little short of breath.

643
00:29:48.745 --> 00:29:51.706
Yeah. you need to walk past
the liquor store. not into it.

644
00:29:51.790 --> 00:29:54.334
Only shape you're getting in
is for a liver transplant.

645
00:29:54.417 --> 00:29:57.337
I don't need a new liver.
Just get rid of this toothache.

646
00:29:57.420 --> 00:29:58.755
Deep breath.

647
00:30:02.634 --> 00:30:04.177
One more.

648
00:30:04.260 --> 00:30:06.763
- Is my heart still ticking?
- Like a jackrabbit.

649
00:30:06.846 --> 00:30:10.016
- How long you been sitting down?
- Oh. just for a few minutes.

650
00:30:10.099 --> 00:30:11.559
Not that long.

651
00:30:11.643 --> 00:30:13.436
Um. Louie...

652
00:30:15.271 --> 00:30:17.440
There's something
I need to tell you.

653
00:30:19.818 --> 00:30:22.987
Last time I saw you.
about ten months ago.

654
00:30:23.071 --> 00:30:27.784
I treated you. and I took
some of your medicine.

655
00:30:27.867 --> 00:30:30.870
I'm not sure I follow.

656
00:30:30.954 --> 00:30:33.540
I have an addiction
to benzos.

657
00:30:33.623 --> 00:30:37.210
and I helped myself to some
of the Librium I prescribed you

658
00:30:37.293 --> 00:30:38.837
for your withdrawal.

659
00:30:38.920 --> 00:30:40.797
You stole my pills?

660
00:30:42.549 --> 00:30:43.967
Yeah.

661
00:30:44.050 --> 00:30:46.469
Yes. um...

662
00:30:46.553 --> 00:30:49.097
I'm sorry.
It was. uh...

663
00:30:49.180 --> 00:30:52.016
it was not only wrong
and utterly unprofessional.

664
00:30:52.100 --> 00:30:54.769
but it was a betrayal
of my Hippocratic Oath.

665
00:30:54.853 --> 00:30:58.022
and it was a fucking crime.

666
00:30:58.106 --> 00:31:02.485
That's where I've been--
rehab and counseling.

667
00:31:04.320 --> 00:31:06.823
- Huh.
- I'm sorry.

668
00:31:06.906 --> 00:31:09.742
I-I understand if you'd prefer
a different doctor.

669
00:31:09.826 --> 00:31:13.162
Hey. Doc.
we have a situation.

670
00:31:13.246 --> 00:31:15.623
Excuse me.

671
00:31:15.707 --> 00:31:17.041
What kind of situation?

672
00:31:17.125 --> 00:31:19.627
Someone left a little baby
in the restroom.

673
00:31:27.886 --> 00:31:29.721
Okay. let's think

674
00:31:29.804 --> 00:31:32.640
about reversible causes
of confusion in the elderly.

675
00:31:32.724 --> 00:31:36.269
Uh. hypo or hypernatremia.
infection. but he's afebrile.

676
00:31:36.352 --> 00:31:38.187
good O2 sats.
and urine dip is negative.

677
00:31:38.271 --> 00:31:42.275
Yeah. great.
Joy. anything to add?

678
00:31:42.358 --> 00:31:44.861
Nah.

679
00:31:44.944 --> 00:31:47.363
- V-tach. Can I--
- Yeah.

680
00:31:49.157 --> 00:31:50.992
No pulse.
Should we call for a code blue?

681
00:31:51.075 --> 00:31:54.996
No CPR. no shock. we honor
his POLST and his wishes.

682
00:31:55.079 --> 00:31:58.583
So what does that leave us?

683
00:31:58.666 --> 00:32:01.210
Making sure he's comfortable.

684
00:32:01.294 --> 00:32:02.754
I'll suction.

685
00:32:02.837 --> 00:32:04.964
Altered mental
in the elderly can also be

686
00:32:05.048 --> 00:32:09.427
toxicity from anticholinergics.
sedative-hypnotics. opioids.

687
00:32:10.929 --> 00:32:13.097
A-am I missing something?

688
00:32:13.181 --> 00:32:15.183
Social skills?

689
00:32:15.266 --> 00:32:17.477
What?

690
00:32:20.104 --> 00:32:21.356
He looks so peaceful.

691
00:32:21.439 --> 00:32:22.565
Shouldn't we go find
a new patient?

692
00:32:22.649 --> 00:32:25.193
No. stay here.

693
00:32:27.070 --> 00:32:29.072
Asystole.

694
00:32:38.039 --> 00:32:40.249
Quick and painless.

695
00:32:40.333 --> 00:32:42.043
We should all be so lucky.

696
00:32:42.126 --> 00:32:44.128
I'll try to contact
some family.

697
00:32:45.797 --> 00:32:49.217
Yeah. one of the things
we like to do here...

698
00:32:52.136 --> 00:32:54.097
When we have the time...

699
00:32:54.180 --> 00:32:56.933
is to take a moment of silence
when we lose a patient

700
00:32:57.016 --> 00:32:59.352
to respect their humanity.

701
00:32:59.435 --> 00:33:03.481
He was someone's son.
perhaps a father himself.

702
00:33:03.564 --> 00:33:06.025
a brother or a friend.

703
00:33:08.820 --> 00:33:12.198
Oh. uh. make sure
your phones are on silent.

704
00:33:16.369 --> 00:33:18.955
Great. great. great.
Okay. Uh...

705
00:33:19.038 --> 00:33:22.375
Is anyone missing a baby?

706
00:33:22.458 --> 00:33:26.713
Did anyone leave their child
in the restroom?

707
00:33:26.796 --> 00:33:30.216
Do you. uh. remember seeing
a woman enter with a baby

708
00:33:30.299 --> 00:33:32.093
but leave without one?

709
00:33:32.176 --> 00:33:34.387
No. sorry.

710
00:33:34.470 --> 00:33:36.389
Might be on the security tapes.

711
00:33:36.472 --> 00:33:38.641
- I'll have Ahmad check it out.
- Please.

712
00:33:38.725 --> 00:33:39.809
Yeah.

713
00:33:39.892 --> 00:33:42.145
Harlow Graham to window one.

714
00:33:42.228 --> 00:33:45.481
Harlow Graham to window one.

715
00:33:45.565 --> 00:33:49.485
Harlow Graham to window one.
please.

716
00:33:54.323 --> 00:33:55.992
Donnie Donahue.
nurse practitioner.

717
00:33:56.075 --> 00:33:57.410
This is Emma. new grad nurse.

718
00:33:57.493 --> 00:33:58.953
- Hey.
- Nice to meet you.

719
00:33:59.037 --> 00:34:00.788
- What's going on?
- Somebody dumped their kid.

720
00:34:00.872 --> 00:34:03.416
Maybe Mom just stepped out
for a smoke or something.

721
00:34:03.499 --> 00:34:05.209
What?
I'm being helpful.

722
00:34:05.293 --> 00:34:06.753
Sometimes they just need
a little break.

723
00:34:06.836 --> 00:34:09.213
and then they come back.

724
00:34:09.297 --> 00:34:10.840
At least they didn't leave her
in a suitcase

725
00:34:10.923 --> 00:34:13.217
- at the bus station.
- Does that happen?

726
00:34:13.301 --> 00:34:15.094
If that's a true story.
I don't want to know about it.

727
00:34:15.178 --> 00:34:17.221
- It ain't the worst I've seen.
- Please. don't tell me.

728
00:34:17.305 --> 00:34:19.682
- I'm a new dad. remember?
- Okay.

729
00:34:26.689 --> 00:34:28.608
There you go.
I'll get Robby.

730
00:34:28.691 --> 00:34:30.318
- Should I come with?
- No. stay here.

731
00:34:30.401 --> 00:34:32.653
Donnie. Jesse.
teach her something.

732
00:34:35.406 --> 00:34:39.077
You know how to check
a rectal temp on an infant?

733
00:34:39.160 --> 00:34:40.703
Uh...

734
00:34:40.787 --> 00:34:42.663
theoretically.

735
00:34:48.211 --> 00:34:51.005
Mr. Williams. how's the pain?

736
00:34:51.089 --> 00:34:52.632
Nothing I can't manage

737
00:34:52.715 --> 00:34:54.634
with some Vicodin
and a little scotch.

738
00:34:54.717 --> 00:34:57.220
Well. it's best
not to mix the two.

739
00:34:57.303 --> 00:34:59.555
James here is going to take you
to get an X-ray of your wrist.

740
00:34:59.639 --> 00:35:01.474
I'm going to be fine.

741
00:35:01.557 --> 00:35:03.935
Well. it'll tell us
if you need a cast.

742
00:35:04.018 --> 00:35:05.603
Oh. I doubt it.

743
00:35:05.686 --> 00:35:07.855
I should probably go home.
keep some ice on it.

744
00:35:07.939 --> 00:35:10.650
I know you guys
always need the beds.

745
00:35:10.733 --> 00:35:13.027
Well. uh.
it'll only take a minute.

746
00:35:13.111 --> 00:35:14.737
and then we'll know for sure.

747
00:35:14.821 --> 00:35:16.864
Yeah. I-I really don't think
it's necessary.

748
00:35:16.948 --> 00:35:19.450
And I have a busy day.
but I appreciate your concern.

749
00:35:22.745 --> 00:35:25.206
I'd really like to observe you
for a little bit.

750
00:35:25.289 --> 00:35:27.792
in case you did hit your head.

751
00:35:27.875 --> 00:35:29.377
My head?

752
00:35:29.460 --> 00:35:31.838
I hit my schnoz on my arm.
I think. nothing more.

753
00:35:31.921 --> 00:35:34.132
You think?
You don't remember?

754
00:35:34.215 --> 00:35:35.591
No.

755
00:35:35.675 --> 00:35:37.426
Or. yes.

756
00:35:37.510 --> 00:35:40.471
I'm going to be fine. really.

757
00:35:40.555 --> 00:35:42.765
But thank you for your concern.

758
00:35:46.519 --> 00:35:48.229
Okay.

759
00:35:50.606 --> 00:35:54.193
How about we take that X-ray
just to be safe?

760
00:35:54.277 --> 00:35:56.696
- Yeah. Yeah. okay.
- Yeah?

761
00:35:56.779 --> 00:35:58.906
- Okay.
- Okay. good idea.

762
00:36:00.908 --> 00:36:02.910
- Somebody found a baby?
- Yeah.

763
00:36:02.994 --> 00:36:05.288
Not the first time
it's happened.

764
00:36:05.371 --> 00:36:07.165
So. about those pills I took--

765
00:36:07.248 --> 00:36:10.209
Oh. don't worry
about it. Doc.

766
00:36:10.293 --> 00:36:13.588
If the pills helped you. great.

767
00:36:13.671 --> 00:36:15.798
I never really liked
taking 'em.

768
00:36:17.842 --> 00:36:19.343
I appreciate that. Louie.

769
00:36:19.427 --> 00:36:21.345
That's not really
the point. but...

770
00:36:21.429 --> 00:36:23.764
I need to lift up
your shirt for a second.

771
00:36:29.812 --> 00:36:32.106
How long has your belly
been hard like that?

772
00:36:32.190 --> 00:36:33.566
I don't know.

773
00:36:33.649 --> 00:36:35.693
I figured I could wait
another week.

774
00:36:35.776 --> 00:36:37.737
You need. uh. some lab tests

775
00:36:37.820 --> 00:36:40.573
and a procedure to drain off
some of this fluid.

776
00:36:40.656 --> 00:36:42.575
Yeah. I know the drill.

777
00:36:42.658 --> 00:36:44.952
I've been tapped
a few times before.

778
00:36:45.036 --> 00:36:48.164
Three times
in the last six months.

779
00:36:48.247 --> 00:36:50.958
You need to give your liver
a break. Louie.

780
00:36:51.042 --> 00:36:52.418
Yeah. I know.

781
00:36:57.048 --> 00:36:58.966
I just heard somebody
dumped a baby

782
00:36:59.050 --> 00:37:00.384
in the waiting-room bathroom.

783
00:37:00.468 --> 00:37:03.596
- How sad is that?
- Huh?

784
00:37:03.679 --> 00:37:06.682
What's up with you today.
Mel...ancholia?

785
00:37:06.766 --> 00:37:09.143
What makes you think
there's something up with me?

786
00:37:09.227 --> 00:37:10.937
You're moping
around here all day

787
00:37:11.020 --> 00:37:13.397
like somebody gunned down
your favorite K-Pop band.

788
00:37:13.481 --> 00:37:15.399
I don't really have
a favorite K-Pop band.

789
00:37:15.483 --> 00:37:17.235
It's not that I don't like
the genre.

790
00:37:17.318 --> 00:37:18.986
- It's just kinda--
- Okay. forget K-Pop.

791
00:37:19.070 --> 00:37:20.613
What's going on with you?

792
00:37:20.696 --> 00:37:21.989
You usually ride in here

793
00:37:22.073 --> 00:37:23.783
on your unicorn
tossing wildflowers.

794
00:37:23.866 --> 00:37:26.494
- "Unicorn"?
- Never mind.

795
00:37:26.577 --> 00:37:28.996
Is everything okay
with your sister?

796
00:37:29.080 --> 00:37:30.706
Oh. yeah. she's great.

797
00:37:30.790 --> 00:37:32.792
It's just this...

798
00:37:34.543 --> 00:37:36.629
Spill. girl.

799
00:37:36.712 --> 00:37:38.256
Um...

800
00:37:38.339 --> 00:37:41.634
well. a-a couple months ago.
I got named in a...

801
00:37:41.717 --> 00:37:43.803
Malpractice lawsuit.

802
00:37:43.886 --> 00:37:47.682
And so. um. today
is the--the deposition.

803
00:37:47.765 --> 00:37:49.392
That's it?

804
00:37:49.475 --> 00:37:52.561
Every emergency-medicine doc
gets sued sooner or later.

805
00:37:52.645 --> 00:37:54.981
Seriously. don't sweat it.
You're still a resident.

806
00:37:55.064 --> 00:37:56.649
We're protected
by the hospital.

807
00:37:56.732 --> 00:38:00.486
You could cut somebody's head
off and get away with it.

808
00:38:00.569 --> 00:38:02.905
But. you know. like. don't.

809
00:38:02.989 --> 00:38:05.366
You don't want to become
known as the one

810
00:38:05.449 --> 00:38:07.952
who put Mel in mel-practice.

811
00:38:08.035 --> 00:38:10.746
Hey. Santos. our little girl.
Kylie. has been

812
00:38:10.830 --> 00:38:14.041
in the West Penn Emergency
Department a couple times.

813
00:38:14.125 --> 00:38:16.669
I'm not saying this
is necessarily the case here.

814
00:38:16.752 --> 00:38:19.463
but recent studies
have linked bullying behavior

815
00:38:19.547 --> 00:38:22.383
to different
personality disorders.

816
00:38:22.466 --> 00:38:25.052
On the other hand. though.
I-I am known to be a bit

817
00:38:25.136 --> 00:38:26.512
overly sensitive sometimes--

818
00:38:26.595 --> 00:38:27.722
- Mel.
- Yes?

819
00:38:27.805 --> 00:38:29.056
You're talking
to yourself again.

820
00:38:29.140 --> 00:38:30.891
- You need something?
- Uh. yeah. a good lawyer.

821
00:38:30.975 --> 00:38:32.685
I don't know. I'm kidding.

822
00:38:32.768 --> 00:38:34.020
I'm--

823
00:38:35.980 --> 00:38:38.107
Yo. Robinavitch. somebody
ditched a bundle of joy

824
00:38:38.190 --> 00:38:39.400
in chairs.

825
00:38:39.483 --> 00:38:40.860
- How old?
- Couple months maybe.

826
00:38:40.943 --> 00:38:42.278
Donahue's got her in Pedes.

827
00:38:42.361 --> 00:38:44.739
- No one saw who left her?
- Apparently not.

828
00:38:44.822 --> 00:38:46.490
- That's so sad.
- Tell me about it.

829
00:38:46.574 --> 00:38:48.034
Who throws away
a perfectly good baby?

830
00:38:49.285 --> 00:38:50.578
Make a lane!

831
00:38:50.661 --> 00:38:53.080
Ah. sweet baby Jesus.
Antoine!

832
00:38:53.164 --> 00:38:55.207
- Right to the outdoor shower!
- I just drive 'em.

833
00:38:55.291 --> 00:38:56.667
I'm not
a wash and detail service.

834
00:38:56.751 --> 00:38:59.045
Yeah. yeah.
God forbid you prove useful.

835
00:38:59.128 --> 00:39:00.629
Ah. good timing. Ms. Emma.

836
00:39:00.713 --> 00:39:03.341
Time for you and me to do
the Lord's work. This way.

837
00:39:03.424 --> 00:39:05.259
Ooh. God. what is that?

838
00:39:05.343 --> 00:39:09.013
Okay. big breath.

839
00:39:09.096 --> 00:39:13.017
All right. lungs sound great.
Can you lean forward for me?

840
00:39:18.606 --> 00:39:22.276
Uh. did you hit your back
when you fell down the stairs?

841
00:39:22.360 --> 00:39:23.402
No.

842
00:39:23.486 --> 00:39:25.279
Okay. there's
a pretty good bruise here.

843
00:39:25.363 --> 00:39:27.198
I got knocked down in soccer.

844
00:39:29.241 --> 00:39:32.036
Oh. no. you broke your wrist
last year. too. huh?

845
00:39:32.119 --> 00:39:34.830
Fell off my skateboard.
Got a purple cast.

846
00:39:34.914 --> 00:39:36.457
Cool color.

847
00:39:36.540 --> 00:39:38.417
And you were treated
at West Penn?

848
00:39:38.501 --> 00:39:40.878
Is that your closest hospital?

849
00:39:40.961 --> 00:39:42.630
Uh. I guess
that would make sense.

850
00:39:42.713 --> 00:39:44.632
I've only been dating her dad
a few months.

851
00:39:44.715 --> 00:39:47.385
Uh. he lived in Garfield
before the divorce.

852
00:39:47.468 --> 00:39:49.887
- And. uh. what about these?
- Soccer.

853
00:39:49.970 --> 00:39:51.597
Do you wear shin guards?

854
00:39:51.680 --> 00:39:53.265
My dad ordered them.

855
00:39:53.349 --> 00:39:56.644
Okay. What does your dad do
for work?

856
00:39:56.727 --> 00:39:59.522
He draws buildings.
but he's not an architect.

857
00:39:59.605 --> 00:40:01.941
He's a draftsman
for a firm in Newcastle.

858
00:40:02.024 --> 00:40:06.362
Okay. Um. Kylie.
any chance you can pee?

859
00:40:06.445 --> 00:40:08.781
- Mm. maybe.
- Okay.

860
00:40:08.864 --> 00:40:10.825
Well. with the bruise
on your back.

861
00:40:10.908 --> 00:40:12.368
we need to check your urine.

862
00:40:12.451 --> 00:40:14.036
- Okay.
- Okay.

863
00:40:16.956 --> 00:40:19.291
Did you eat anything
out of the ordinary recently?

864
00:40:19.375 --> 00:40:20.709
No.

865
00:40:20.793 --> 00:40:23.170
Sorry. but we went
through this a bunch.

866
00:40:23.254 --> 00:40:24.839
Don't you people communicate?

867
00:40:24.922 --> 00:40:26.715
You're the third nurse
we've told her story to.

868
00:40:26.799 --> 00:40:28.050
I'm a doctor.

869
00:40:28.134 --> 00:40:31.095
Richard. would you go
to the cafeteria

870
00:40:31.178 --> 00:40:33.514
and get me
a large chamomile tea?

871
00:40:33.597 --> 00:40:35.683
What can we get you. my dear?

872
00:40:35.766 --> 00:40:38.060
I'm fine. thank you.

873
00:40:40.062 --> 00:40:41.856
Yeah. I'll be right back.

874
00:40:45.734 --> 00:40:48.070
Please excuse my son.

875
00:40:48.154 --> 00:40:49.989
Ever since my husband died.

876
00:40:50.072 --> 00:40:52.408
he's been
a little overprotective.

877
00:40:52.491 --> 00:40:54.452
I think it's sweet.

878
00:40:54.535 --> 00:40:57.371
- You're very lucky to have him.
- I am.

879
00:40:58.998 --> 00:41:02.835
Are you still taking your
loperamide and cholestyramine?

880
00:41:02.918 --> 00:41:05.629
Um. mm. not so much.

881
00:41:05.713 --> 00:41:07.339
No?

882
00:41:07.423 --> 00:41:09.758
That may be why you're
experiencing the abdominal pain

883
00:41:09.842 --> 00:41:11.385
and vomiting.

884
00:41:11.469 --> 00:41:13.596
When did you stop taking
your meds?

885
00:41:13.679 --> 00:41:15.848
Last winter or so.

886
00:41:17.892 --> 00:41:21.437
My neighbor Helen and I bingo
in Wintersville.

887
00:41:21.520 --> 00:41:24.148
There's a dispensary next door.

888
00:41:24.231 --> 00:41:26.192
And we got some marijuana.

889
00:41:26.275 --> 00:41:30.446
And I swear
it cleared everything up.

890
00:41:30.529 --> 00:41:34.033
A few cookies
every few hours...

891
00:41:34.116 --> 00:41:36.702
and no more pain.

892
00:41:36.785 --> 00:41:39.246
"A few cookies"?

893
00:41:39.330 --> 00:41:41.373
How many are you eating
in a day?

894
00:41:41.457 --> 00:41:43.459
Oh. uh...

895
00:41:43.542 --> 00:41:46.128
I don't know.

896
00:41:46.212 --> 00:41:51.050
Probably a dozen or so.
but they're not very big.

897
00:41:51.133 --> 00:41:53.052
There have been some studies

898
00:41:53.135 --> 00:41:55.262
that show
an added dementia risk

899
00:41:55.346 --> 00:41:58.307
with marijuana use
in older adults.

900
00:41:59.725 --> 00:42:02.353
Well. that sucks
for old people.

901
00:42:03.771 --> 00:42:05.648
Kylie.
there are some questions

902
00:42:05.731 --> 00:42:09.693
that we ask every kid
who comes in with an injury.

903
00:42:09.777 --> 00:42:11.237
Like what?

904
00:42:11.320 --> 00:42:14.698
Like. sometimes the people
that you live with

905
00:42:14.782 --> 00:42:19.703
can get so mad that
they hit you or hurt you.

906
00:42:19.787 --> 00:42:21.914
maybe without even meaning to.

907
00:42:21.997 --> 00:42:23.374
Does that ever happen?

908
00:42:23.457 --> 00:42:25.834
No. not to me.

909
00:42:25.918 --> 00:42:28.087
Or sometimes kids
can get punished

910
00:42:28.170 --> 00:42:29.713
for doing something wrong

911
00:42:29.797 --> 00:42:33.259
with maybe a spanking
or a belt.

912
00:42:33.342 --> 00:42:35.928
I get time-outs.

913
00:42:36.011 --> 00:42:38.055
How about at school. Kylie?

914
00:42:38.138 --> 00:42:41.517
You know. is anybody being.
you know. mean or bullying you?

915
00:42:41.600 --> 00:42:44.186
No. I have lots of friends.

916
00:43:05.040 --> 00:43:07.126
Yo. Whitaker.

917
00:43:07.209 --> 00:43:09.962
Dr. Langdon.

918
00:43:10.045 --> 00:43:13.757
- You. uh. meet Louie here?
- Uh. yeah. yeah. many times.

919
00:43:13.841 --> 00:43:16.135
- Good morning. Mr. Cloverfield.
- What's up. Doc?

920
00:43:16.218 --> 00:43:18.345
Where's your new resident
badge buddy. buddy?

921
00:43:18.429 --> 00:43:22.683
Oh. uh. yeah. they--they
didn't give me a new one yet.

922
00:43:22.766 --> 00:43:24.018
Bummer.

923
00:43:24.101 --> 00:43:25.561
You and. uh.
your ducklings got time

924
00:43:25.644 --> 00:43:27.271
to tap a six-pack
off our friend here?

925
00:43:27.354 --> 00:43:29.815
- Louie needs a paracentesis.
- Yeah. sure.

926
00:43:29.898 --> 00:43:31.775
It's good to see you
again. Louie--

927
00:43:31.859 --> 00:43:33.527
not in this condition.
of course.

928
00:43:33.611 --> 00:43:34.570
How you feeling?

929
00:43:34.653 --> 00:43:37.948
Feeling like I need
a drink pretty soon.

930
00:43:38.032 --> 00:43:39.783
Okay. well.
first things first--

931
00:43:39.867 --> 00:43:42.036
we are going to make you
more comfortable

932
00:43:42.119 --> 00:43:43.662
by draining some fluid.

933
00:43:43.746 --> 00:43:45.372
You're gonna take off
a big volume.

934
00:43:45.456 --> 00:43:48.500
so start with 60 grams
of 25% albumin IV.

935
00:43:48.584 --> 00:43:51.086
- You tapped him before?
- No.

936
00:43:51.170 --> 00:43:53.589
That's okay. Doc.
I'll talk him through it.

937
00:43:53.672 --> 00:43:55.382
Okay.

938
00:43:57.051 --> 00:44:00.429
Sats 99 on room air.
normal BP. normal pulse.

939
00:44:03.265 --> 00:44:04.850
Oh. well hydrated.

940
00:44:04.933 --> 00:44:06.602
No obvious source
of infection.

941
00:44:06.685 --> 00:44:09.605
Could be a benign virus.
but can't assume that.

942
00:44:09.688 --> 00:44:12.232
- Is this the abandoned baby?
- Mm-hmm.

943
00:44:12.316 --> 00:44:14.610
- How old?
- How old do you think she is?

944
00:44:14.693 --> 00:44:18.030
- Month. month and a half?
- It's tricky.

945
00:44:18.113 --> 00:44:21.408
Under 28 days is a Safe Haven
drop-off. no questions asked.

946
00:44:21.492 --> 00:44:24.870
But over 28 days is a crime.
child abandonment.

947
00:44:24.953 --> 00:44:27.039
How should we assess?

948
00:44:27.122 --> 00:44:30.125
Under 28 days gets everything.
including an LP.

949
00:44:30.209 --> 00:44:32.461
But over 28 days.

950
00:44:32.544 --> 00:44:34.630
you can follow PECARN
or Step-by-step

951
00:44:34.713 --> 00:44:37.383
to determine risk of invasive
bacterial infection.

952
00:44:37.466 --> 00:44:38.884
This baby looks great.

953
00:44:38.967 --> 00:44:40.844
But we know nothing
about the birth history.

954
00:44:40.928 --> 00:44:44.640
Did Mom have group B strep.
active HSV lesions?

955
00:44:44.723 --> 00:44:48.727
We should assume the worst.
Put in your orders. Dr. Mohan.

956
00:44:48.811 --> 00:44:50.771
CBC...

957
00:44:50.854 --> 00:44:53.273
Blood culture. chem panel.

958
00:44:53.357 --> 00:44:56.151
chest X-ray. UA and culture.

959
00:44:56.235 --> 00:44:58.362
respiratory virus panel.

960
00:44:58.445 --> 00:45:02.658
Check inflammatory markers--
procalcitonin and CRP--

961
00:45:02.741 --> 00:45:04.743
then take it from there.

962
00:45:04.827 --> 00:45:06.954
That sounds like a plan.

963
00:45:07.037 --> 00:45:09.123
Dr. Robby.
Santos needs you in North 1.

964
00:45:09.206 --> 00:45:10.666
Okay. I'll be right there.

965
00:45:10.749 --> 00:45:13.168
If you'll excuse me.
if you'll excuse me.

966
00:45:15.546 --> 00:45:19.717
- Mind if I join with?
- Uh. no. I got this.

967
00:45:19.800 --> 00:45:21.468
It will help me
get a better sense

968
00:45:21.552 --> 00:45:23.679
of how you like to do things
by seeing you in action

969
00:45:23.762 --> 00:45:25.222
with the residents.

970
00:45:25.305 --> 00:45:26.974
Be my guest.

971
00:45:29.727 --> 00:45:31.895
I will be right back.

972
00:45:37.025 --> 00:45:39.695
Um. nine-year-old
Kylie Connors--

973
00:45:39.778 --> 00:45:41.780
took a tumble running up
the stairs this morning.

974
00:45:41.864 --> 00:45:43.532
Chin lac and fractured tooth.

975
00:45:43.615 --> 00:45:45.784
Brought in by her dad's
girlfriend. Gina.

976
00:45:45.868 --> 00:45:48.912
Supposedly. the dad had
to leave early for work.

977
00:45:48.996 --> 00:45:51.707
Kylie has a lot of bruising
on her body--

978
00:45:51.790 --> 00:45:53.292
some old. some new.

979
00:45:53.375 --> 00:45:56.879
Are you concerned
about non-accidental trauma?

980
00:45:56.962 --> 00:45:58.505
Or worse.

981
00:45:58.589 --> 00:46:00.966
Her urine sample shows
gross hematuria.

982
00:46:01.049 --> 00:46:04.178
which could be renal injury.
or vaginal bleeding from trauma

983
00:46:04.261 --> 00:46:06.430
could have contaminated
the specimen.

984
00:46:06.513 --> 00:46:09.349
Lots to consider.
What's your plan?

985
00:46:09.433 --> 00:46:12.019
Labs. ultrasound.
social-work consult.

986
00:46:12.102 --> 00:46:14.062
then decide
if this is reportable.

987
00:46:14.146 --> 00:46:15.522
Mm-hmm.

988
00:46:18.776 --> 00:46:20.527
Let me know
if you can feel this.

989
00:46:20.611 --> 00:46:22.362
No.
Am I supposed to?

990
00:46:22.446 --> 00:46:23.614
No.

991
00:46:27.868 --> 00:46:29.953
Your hair's
such a pretty color.

992
00:46:30.037 --> 00:46:31.163
Thank you.

993
00:46:31.246 --> 00:46:33.665
Reminds me of my mom.

994
00:46:33.749 --> 00:46:36.960
- She died when I was nine.
- Oh. I'm sorry about that.

995
00:46:37.044 --> 00:46:39.546
She wore glasses
like you. too.

996
00:46:39.630 --> 00:46:41.548
Weird.

997
00:46:41.632 --> 00:46:44.927
What do you like to do
when you're not working?

998
00:46:45.010 --> 00:46:47.387
Um. spend some time
with my sister.

999
00:46:47.471 --> 00:46:49.181
read.

1000
00:46:49.264 --> 00:46:50.766
Do you drink coffee?

1001
00:46:50.849 --> 00:46:54.436
Uh. no. I avoid caffeine.

1002
00:46:54.520 --> 00:46:55.562
Me too.

1003
00:46:55.646 --> 00:46:57.231
Um...

1004
00:46:57.314 --> 00:46:59.274
what about boba?

1005
00:47:00.859 --> 00:47:04.321
I love boba.

1006
00:47:06.990 --> 00:47:08.909
I'd offer you some gum.
but it's laced with nicotine.

1007
00:47:08.992 --> 00:47:10.786
Trying to quit smoking.

1008
00:47:10.869 --> 00:47:13.372
That's good.

1009
00:47:13.455 --> 00:47:15.123
Verdict's still out.

1010
00:47:15.207 --> 00:47:17.501
Get in all those nooks
and crannies. Mr. Digby.

1011
00:47:17.584 --> 00:47:19.378
Your skin will thank you.

1012
00:47:19.461 --> 00:47:21.296
We all will.

1013
00:47:21.380 --> 00:47:25.300
Oh. I could stay
in here all day.

1014
00:47:25.384 --> 00:47:27.594
It's a miracle what little
soap. water. and human decency

1015
00:47:27.678 --> 00:47:29.596
can do sometimes.

1016
00:47:29.680 --> 00:47:31.014
Don't forget the ears. pal.

1017
00:47:31.098 --> 00:47:32.975
Don't want anything
growing in there either.

1018
00:47:33.058 --> 00:47:34.601
Okay. Okay.

1019
00:47:34.685 --> 00:47:36.520
What's your story. Emma?

1020
00:47:36.603 --> 00:47:39.398
What'd your parents do?
Got siblings? Boyfriend?

1021
00:47:39.481 --> 00:47:42.317
Ever kill a man in a bar fight?

1022
00:47:42.401 --> 00:47:43.694
Uh...

1023
00:47:53.161 --> 00:47:55.414
So. Mr. Williams.

1024
00:47:55.497 --> 00:47:57.833
sometimes a fracture
of the scaphoid bone

1025
00:47:57.916 --> 00:47:59.710
doesn't show up on day one.

1026
00:47:59.793 --> 00:48:03.422
So my advice to be safe is
wear a splint for two weeks

1027
00:48:03.505 --> 00:48:05.632
and then come back
for a repeat X-ray.

1028
00:48:05.716 --> 00:48:07.426
and we'll see
if it's really there.

1029
00:48:09.803 --> 00:48:12.347
My knee hurts.

1030
00:48:12.431 --> 00:48:15.684
Oh. did you hurt your knee?

1031
00:48:15.767 --> 00:48:17.477
I must have.

1032
00:48:24.067 --> 00:48:26.069
What is this?

1033
00:48:26.153 --> 00:48:28.989
That's. um. for your wrist.

1034
00:48:29.072 --> 00:48:31.909
And I need this?

1035
00:48:31.992 --> 00:48:34.661
Well. um. if it's a. uh--

1036
00:48:34.745 --> 00:48:36.705
John. can you?

1037
00:48:36.788 --> 00:48:39.291
If it's a fracture
and we don't immobilize.

1038
00:48:39.374 --> 00:48:41.543
the bone might not heal
properly.

1039
00:48:43.545 --> 00:48:47.299
How long is this gonna take?

1040
00:48:47.382 --> 00:48:49.760
Just a few minutes
to fit you.

1041
00:48:52.679 --> 00:48:55.140
Is this place new?

1042
00:48:57.893 --> 00:49:01.855
Mr. Williams.
do you know what day it is?

1043
00:49:05.442 --> 00:49:07.903
It's Taco Tuesday.

1044
00:49:07.986 --> 00:49:10.197
Do you know where you are?

1045
00:49:11.740 --> 00:49:14.910
Yeah. I'm in the slowest
medical clinic in the West.

1046
00:49:14.993 --> 00:49:17.371
Do you know what year it is?

1047
00:49:17.454 --> 00:49:19.498
How about you just
fix my wrist

1048
00:49:19.581 --> 00:49:23.710
and you stop
with all the questions?

1049
00:49:23.794 --> 00:49:26.838
I am not here to be profiled.

1050
00:49:31.051 --> 00:49:33.887
Yeah. of course.

1051
00:49:33.971 --> 00:49:36.056
I'll be back. okay?

1052
00:49:46.817 --> 00:49:49.444
All right. Mr. Digby.
looking better already.

1053
00:49:49.528 --> 00:49:51.405
Certainly smell
a little better.

1054
00:49:51.488 --> 00:49:52.906
Do you have any conditioner?

1055
00:49:52.990 --> 00:49:55.033
Let's get you dried off
and back inside.

1056
00:49:55.117 --> 00:49:56.702
Get him gowned up
and put him in South 21.

1057
00:49:56.785 --> 00:49:57.869
across from the old nun.

1058
00:49:57.953 --> 00:50:01.164
Maybe some of her divine grace
will wear off on him.

1059
00:50:01.248 --> 00:50:02.499
Who do we have here?

1060
00:50:02.582 --> 00:50:05.419
Evelyn Bostick. 81.
with Alzheimer's.

1061
00:50:05.502 --> 00:50:07.671
We brought her husband in
about 30 minutes ago.

1062
00:50:07.754 --> 00:50:09.297
She was supposed
to get a ride in.

1063
00:50:09.381 --> 00:50:10.966
but they found her
wandering in traffic.

1064
00:50:11.049 --> 00:50:13.010
- Where are we?
- You're at the hospital. dear.

1065
00:50:13.093 --> 00:50:14.386
I'm not sick.

1066
00:50:14.469 --> 00:50:16.388
We brought you
to see your husband.

1067
00:50:16.471 --> 00:50:18.390
Oh. no.
Is Ethan okay?

1068
00:50:18.473 --> 00:50:20.976
I'll be in to chat with you.
Mrs. Bostick.

1069
00:50:21.059 --> 00:50:23.520
He died.

1070
00:50:23.603 --> 00:50:25.397
What you got. Amboy?

1071
00:50:25.480 --> 00:50:28.608
Allen Billings--had a pallet
fall onto his outstretched arm.

1072
00:50:28.692 --> 00:50:31.028
- Looks like an open dislocation.
- Yeah. that's got to hurt.

1073
00:50:31.111 --> 00:50:32.738
Don't worry. sir.
We got you.

1074
00:50:38.869 --> 00:50:41.997
- How's she doing?
- Seems happy enough.

1075
00:50:42.080 --> 00:50:43.999
- Yeah. Hi.
- Hi.

1076
00:50:44.082 --> 00:50:46.793
Just got a quick
point-of-care CBC.

1077
00:50:53.300 --> 00:50:55.260
Is there a problem?

1078
00:50:58.805 --> 00:51:00.557
Did I miss something?

1079
00:51:00.640 --> 00:51:03.602
Dr. Al? Dr. Al?
